profileAlternative.summary:
Business Development director at Solar Design Associates. Founded in 1974 by noted solar advocate, designer and author Steven J. Strong, Solar Design Associates has earned a global reputation for its pioneering leadership in the renewable energy field.

Solar Design works with architects, engineers and commercial building owners, as well as private and institutional clients, in the quest for excellence and innovation in solar electric, solar thermal and wind energy systems.

SDA continues to build alliances with solar power developers and electric utilities. Our pioneering work in building integration (BIPV) keeps us in the forefront of sustainable energy product development and zero-energy building design.

Formerly developed solar power projects through third party financing (PPA) model with SolarPowerPartners.

Former registered representative, Progressive Asset Management Network & Financial West Group, FINRA/SIPC;
Managed assets of individuals, non profits, small companies, with individual brokerage accounts, retirement plans including 401K, IRA-SEP, SIMPLE plans, 529 college savings plans, with a focus on socially and environmentally responsible investments;

Former builder, sales manager, designer for passive solar residential additions in Eastern Massachusetts;

Member Natural Resource Defense Council Environmental Entrepreneurs New England Chapter;

Twenty years experience in residential solar construction, sales and design, Three years with solar hot water sales and marketing. Four years in public policy work in Federal and State Energy offices dealing with financing conservation and renewable energy projects;

Formerly Registered Rep. (Mass), Series 7 and 66; Valid Mass Construction Supervisor license,
Master in City and Regional Planning Harvard University 1981, BA University of Pennsylvania (Anthropology) 1978;

